divs: Sighting DetailsOn the 16th of November 2009, at around 9:30pm I was walking my dog around the Oval in Pretwick, Scotland. I was suddenly aware of a strange tension in the air and my hair began to stand on end, beneth the many layers I had wrapped up in because of the winter weather. My dog, Saber, an Alsatian, began to cower in fear of some unseen object overhead, and began to pull on the leash. I was suddenly very light headed and saw several different combinations of flashing lights above me. I woke up outside the swimming pool in Prestwick six hours later, my eyes bloodshot and with an orange liquid coming from my nose.

Summary: Large, metallic, covered in different coloured flashing lights.
